snippet.textDisplay:
Just in case no-one else has pointed this out in another comment, it is VERY IMPORTANT to know, and understand, that Novax Djocovid had two other options for complying with requirements for qualifying for a visa to enter Australia:

1 - provide proof of vaccination with the completed visa application form.

2 - admit to being unvaccinated and arrive in Australia long enough before the event he was coming for to be able to spend the required length of time in a quarantine facility undergoing the necessary PCR testing regime before being allowed out in public.

Instead of choosing one of those two options, he signed a visa application form that claimed he had a medical exemption from vaccination, but was not able to provide proof of that exemption when asked to do so by the immigration officials upon arrival.

What do you think would happen to you, me or any other 'regular' person in that situation?

The problems really started when another Border Security officer signed the paperwork revoking his visa about 40 minutes earlier than the time he was told he had until to organise somebody to provide the proof of exemption required.
